<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Plenteous" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Plenteous,</orth> copious, exuberant, abundant: <cit><quote>her p. womb expresseth his full tilth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 4, 43</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a most p. crop,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.5.101" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 5, 101</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>Ceres' p. load,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 2, 2</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>p. tears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.70" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 70</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>honour and p. safety,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.104" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 104</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to gratulate thy p. bosom,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 1.2.131" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 2, 131</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>made p. wounds,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 3.5.66" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 66</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>from forth thy p. bosom,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.186" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 186</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my p. joys,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 4, 33</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with p. rivers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 66</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of so high and p. wit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.201" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 201</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>